We need to prove that for a graph $G$ where any subgraph on $k$ vertices has at most $2k-3$ edges, if $H$ has $m$ edges and no isolated vertices, then $\hat{r}(G,H) \ll m$. In other words, we need to show that $G$ is Ramsey size linear.

